(272, 1, '2014-06-17 14:10:20', '2014-06-17 14:10:20', '<b>Designated Crossing Areas</b>\r\n\r\nWhen livestock or farm equipment travel through watercourses, it can have a negative impact on the water quality downstream, as well as seriously erode the streambanks. By limiting crossing areas to only designated areas (i.e. fencing livestock out of the rest of the water course) it is possible to reduce these impacts.\r\n\r\nBuilding a crossing point that is less susceptible to erosion is another option. This could be achieved through the building of a bridge, or by building a crossing area that is built up to withstand the weight of equipment traffic<span style="color: #ff0000;">. MORE INSTRUCTIONS TO COME.</span>\r\n\r\nIt should be noted, however, that <b>ANY</b> alteration to a stream or watercourse, <b>including bridges</b>, does require permission through the navigable waters act (1985). More information, as well as the appropriate paperwork, can be found <strong><a href="https://www.novascotia.ca/snsmr/paal/nse/paal181.asp">here</a></strong>.', 'Water Crossing', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '247-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 14:10:20', '2014-06-17 14:10:20', '', 247, 'http://localhost/farming/?p=272', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(273, 1, '2014-06-17 14:11:29', '2014-06-17 14:11:29', '<i><b>Reducing or limiting access to riparian areas from livestock</b></i>\r\n\r\nLivestock trample riparian areas, this reduces the function of riparian vegetation resulting in increased susceptibility to erosion and flooding, and reduced water quality. Furthermore, the feces and urine from livestock will have a direct impact on water quality.\r\n\r\nThere are different ways that you can limit the number of livestock that enter your watercourses. Depending on what your goals are (simply improving water quality, or improving water quality and terrestrial habitat) the way that these different activities are carried out may vary.', 'Limiting Livestock Access to Waterway''s ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '250-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-06-17 14:11:29', '2014-06-17 14:11:29', '', 250, 'http://localhost/farming/?p=273', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
